  						<table border='0' cellpadding='3' cellspacing='0' width='92%'>
	<tr>
	  <td width='100%' bgcolor='#0E024D' class='spti2' align='center'>SWIFTTAIL, THE TALE OF SLEAT. CHAPTER 10</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	  <td width='100%'><font face='verdana' size='2pt'><P>Sleat runs across the open fields knee high grass whips at his legs the cool night air whistles past his ear holes he parts his lips and lets the night air flow over his tongue, he slows his pace wood smoke and cooked meat drift on the breeze.
Sleat lowers his head his jaws open as he blows great puffs of air out of his nose and mouth, his smelling glands are purged of all the old smells he lifts his snout and inhales deeply the smoke is strong in this direction he runs south.</P>

<P>Sleat crests a small rise, the ancient ruins glow from the small fire that burns in the center of the main structure Sleat edges foreword he smells Iskar and cooking meat, he smiles to himself his sharp teeth glow in the moonlight.
Sleat drifts thru the shadows the night opens itself to him as he moves silently up to the wall, he looks over at 4 bandits they sit around the fire cooking the haunch of a saber tooth kit, the bandits hiss and shout at each other each trying to prove dominance over the others.</P>

<P>Sleat looks for guards and sees none, these stupid bandits will pay with their life’s, sleats watches as one of the bandits grunts and rises he wonders off into the night Sleat shadows him, the bandit stops just out of hearing of his companions and starts to relief himself.
The silk wrapped baton crashes into the bandits spine just below his spiked ridge, it’s body falls to the ground, legs twitches as the Iksar dies his clawed toes digging into the wet ground, Sleat pulls the sash from the bandits arm and puts it into his bag.
He follows the path the lone bandit walked back to the edge of the fire light, the dead bandits companions their fists full of meat never even looked up as Sleat enters the fire light.</P>

<P>Sleat hisses in disgust at the bandit scum and kicks his foot into the throat of the first bandit he feels a thrill as his long talons rip thru its neck, the bandit gags and grabs his throat as blood sprays from his wrecked neck. The other  two bandits screaming in fear and rage scramble to their feet.
Sleat kicks out at the closest bandit allowing him to jump back away from the kick, the bandits legs hit a small half section of wall and he falls to his back, Sleat whips his tail under the last bandits chin forcing his head to snap back, the bandit staggers its eyes go wide and it falls to its knees.
Sleat turns to the fallen bandit and catches his hand as it thrusts towards sleets stomach he twists the arm and feels the joint tear with a wet popping noise a rusty dagger falls from its dead hand. Sleat jams his elbow into the side of the bandit’s head feeling the bandit’s eye and socket explode from the force of the hit. The bandit falls to the ground dead as the splinters of its skull shred its brain.
Sleat hisses as a dagger slices along his fore arm, Sleat slams his fist into the bandits throat crushing his wind pipe, the bandit turns to run as Sleat shatters its knee with a back kick, the bandits falls clawing at the ground as it slowly suffocates.
Sleat jumps across the fire to the last bandit it is barley alive its hands wrapped around its throat holding its life’s blood from falling to the already large puddle surrounding it. Sleat lifts him up and wraps his arms around the bandit’s snout and twists; he ends its life with a quick snap of a neck.</P>

<P>Sleat drags the bodies to the far side of the ruins and returns to the fire, he kicks sand over the spilled blood and sits down next to the fire he hum’s a little tune he has heard Terra sing as she stitches his wounds, he grabs a piece of meat from the fire and proceeds to look thru his newly found loot, many things he tosses over the wall behind him cheap jewelry and even cheaper armor, the bladed weapons he has no use for so he tosses them also.
Sleat eats the cooked meat and begins to wrap his wounded arm he binds the wound tight and sits and waits soon it will heal and he will continue on his way the night is still very young.</P>

<P>Sleat feels the wounds closing as he hears a shuffling noise outside the ruins his body stiffens, he hears a voice it calls to him in his native language, very rough yet understandable Sleat smiles maybe more bandits have came to see their dead friends.
Sleat lets out a loud grunt, his smile becomes a little wider when he sees a light elf enter the fire light, accompanied by a troll the troll has a human female tethered around the neck her hands are bound in front of her and her back is full with packs and equipment.</P>

<P>Serin enters the camp the filthy Iksar is sitting at the campfire usually there are more yet they may be out beating something up
Or doing what ever it is these stupid creatures do for fun.
Serin fights the urge to scowl at the Iksar as it sits on the ground and just smiles at him, every time he sees them smile he thinks of the saltwater crocs of oasis, mean and ready to eat you.
Serin asks where the others are and it stupidly points deeper into the ruins, the fire dances making weird shadows across the ruins, great he thinks they could be anywhere I sure hope this one has the money… and is as dumb as he looks Serin smiles back at the Iksar maybe I can get double my usual price from this lone Iksar….</P>

<P>Sleat tilts his head, he can tell from the elf’s body posture he thinks little of Sleat, so he plays along, finally the elf blows out a breath and tells Sleat “ ok idiot I am Serin you are to give me 500pp for this slave “ he points to the bound human female, Sleat smile grows larger and he nods…</P>

<P>Serin smiles his mind races dam it I should have asked for 750pp or even 800pp this lizard is so dumb no wonder the others left him to tend the fire. Serin turns and yells at the troll to stop playing with the slave, the toll has man handled the slave for hours, next time he will get a smarter body guard, one that will remember not to touch the merchandise.
 Serin shifts his feet and feels his feet slip he looks down at the blood oozing out of the sand, Serin eyes go wide as he watches the Iksar smile get larger showing row after row of razor sharp teeth…</P>

<P>Sleat watches as the elf yells at the troll. The troll all but ignores the elf and continues to run his hand thru the human’s short hair, pulling large chunks of hair out with each stroke.  Sleat smiles as the elf finally sees the rather large puddle of blood he has been standing in since he arrived, his eyes go wide as Sleat arcs his baton and suppresses a snicker as it lifts the elf off the ground, Terra has told him most races are easily damaged from strikes to the groin area, Sleat is rewarded with a slight squeal of pain as his baton lifts the elf off his feet, Sleat slams his fist into the side of the elf’s head as he jumps to his feet, Sleat pulls back on the power not wanting to kill this elf just yet, he falls to the bloody ground his mouth open and face a strange whitish green.</P>
 
<P>Sleat turns to the troll it still isn’t aware of his failure as a bodyguard, the human females eyes go wide as she watches Serin fall to the ground and she starts to scream, the troll grunts in pain as 3 shirkens appear in his back.
Sleat pulls 3 shirkens and throws them with all his strength they slice into the trolls thick hide, blood streams down its back it roars in pain as it spins around to face Sleat, it claws at the small pieces of metal buried in its back but cant reach them.</P>

<P>The troll pulls a large 2 handed hammer from its belt and charges Sleat the hammer held above his head waiting to crush Sleat to a pulp with one hit, Sleat jumps aside at the last second letting the momentum of the hammer carry the troll past him, Sleat jumps onto the broad back of the troll and slams the 3 shirkens deeper into the trolls back with his baton, with each hit the small stars sink under the trolls skin.</P>

<P>Sleat slams his baton into the side of the troll’s head as he leaps away from its back it roars in pain as the baton shatters the trolls jaw. Sleat lands and turns just in time to have the hammer slam into his chest propelling him across the ruins into the wall.
Sleat feels his body slide down the wall and crumple to the ground, he watches thru dazed eyes as the troll spits out pieces of bone and teeth wipes the blood from its shredded lips and turns to where he is sitting. Sleat wills his body to move yet nothing happens the troll lifts his hammer over its head and heads towards Sleat. Sleat closes his eyes and forces his body to roll, the ground shakes from the hammers hit.  the wall where Sleat was sitting explodes into millions of tiny shards of brick and cement. Sleat rises to his feet and swings his baton with all his strength, the pent up energy from the swing slams into the trolls knee shattering the huge joint, the troll screams in pain as he falls to the ground, Sleat jumps to the trolls back and slams his batons into the trolls head, each hit feels softer and softer the trolls body goes limp its skull miss-shaped, gray matter drips from the skull where the skin has been smashed into oblivion. Sleats body shakes from exhaustion and pain, he feels his ribs they are floating in places, sharp edges threaten to poke thru his skin, his lock jaw vest it torn and stretched from the mighty blow.</P>

<P>Sleat wraps his chest each breath is a fiery pain his body flushes with pleasure, the lock jaw vest is ruined he stuffs it into his pack he looks over at the human female she is curled into the corner trying to hide in the shadows, he tells her in common “ come out and help me you are now a slave of the Swifttails” he presses his hand into the puddle of blood forming around the troll and presses it to her chest, he flick his talons over her bound wrists and frees her hands, he whisper do not run or I will be forced to kill you she nods in understanding, he turns to Serin he is laying in a puddle of his own vomit clutching his groin and whimpering  tie him up before he can put up to much of a fight. He watches as a smile spreads across the females face.</P>

<P>Sleat pulled her off of the elf after he feared she would kill him her kicks where solid and strong causing him to vomit repeatedly and make animal like moans and squeals of pain.
Sleat rummaged thru the trolls equipment taking only what he could carry, he crossed to serin's bag and opened it he pulled out a robe, the likes Sleat had never seen it was cool to the touch woven from a strong light blue fabric the magic’s literally jumped from the robe Sleat pulled it over his head and felt the rush of magic enveloped him it formed to his body becoming wider across his shoulders and longer along the leg. He tingled with power, Sleat smiled he likes this crystal covers shroud.</P>

<P>Sleat stands and heads for the Swiftails compound the sun breaks over the mountain ridge a new day is about to start. Sleat had passed a another test he will live another day to bring glory to his clan, his new human slave following behind him leading Serin his body bloody and beaten limping still holding his groin……………………………………………….</P>

<P>Terra sweeps out Sleats meager hut, she sees her master his stride slow and pained she rushes to his aid, letting him use her to hold some of his weight, he hisses a friendly greeting to her and tells her to see to his new property, he puts his hand on her shoulder I have also brought you a gift my good servant, try not to maim him but let him reap what he sows, Sleat keeps walking to his hut as Terra looks in disbelief at the humbled high elf being dragged thru the Swiftails compound.
Sleat enters his hut and smiles as he hears Terra's raised voice and the sound of the broom handle hitting flesh, maybe now she will be able to put her demons to rest………………………….. </P>

<P>Sleat hisses as she binds his broken ribs tight the pain lessens with each wrap the bones are forced into place, Sleat sees the smile on Terra's lips and hisses in laughter, the pain rolls thru his body, after you are done seeing to my wounds I will have you see to the 2 new slaves, I will not claim the male as mine Sleat feels Terra’s body relax he will become a common slave Terra shivers to be master less in the Iksar city is not healthy, many don’t ever return from their first trip outside the compound.
Sleat smiles the other slave, she is your responsibility I will mark her, see that she learns our ways.
Come let us go to the feast I will have to retell the battle of that I am sure, 4 bandits, one troll and 2 slaves I am afraid what my next trip outside the city walls will bring to my clan ………………………………………………………………………………</P>



<p->Note:
Sleat is one of my characters that I play on bertoxxulous server.
Any feed back would be appreciated you can reach me at lyrak_decorrupter@yahoo.com</p>
 </font></td>
	</tr>
